The paper deals with 3D imaging technologies and statistical shape models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of non-linear optimization also suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the focus on creating human-like shapes from measurements suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
